      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BILLY RAY'S GIRL (2) has been in super consistent form recently with three minors on end before missing the frame latest finishing fourth (30.04) at this track. Solid record here at the distance winning five races. Has good early burn and is drawn to be prominent. Can discover winning form. TARAWI BRUMBY (1) struggled in tougher grade last start at this track, but prior to that won by a nose at Gosford (35.21) beating Sneaky Tycoon in a Grade 5 on June 16. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Has ability and can measure up. JOANNE (4) was strongly supported last start when a short priced favourite and duly saluted winning by 3 lengths at Richmond in a handy 35.43. Jumping from the pinch draw but goes well over this trip. Capable of going well again. TANK KEEPING (6) failed to justify the weight of support last time but cannot be taken lightly.",
